## 6. Styling approach

### Methodology

Layered CSS in `src/app/styles.css` â€” Tailwind utilities beat Astryx component styles:

```
reset â†’ theme â†’ base â†’ astryx-base â†’ astryx-theme â†’ components â†’ utilities
```

Three-tier styling (in priority order):

1. Astryx component props (`variant`, `color`, `gap`)
2. Token-backed Tailwind (`bg-surface`, `text-primary`, `rounded-lg`)
3. Escape hatch: `bg-[var(--color-background-surface)]`

Example from `home.tsx`:

```tsx
<main className="min-h-screen bg-body p-8">
  <VStack gap={8}>
    <Card className="border-2 border-blue-500 shadow-lg">
      <Text type="body">Token-backed layout + Astryx override</Text>
    </Card>
    <div className="rounded-lg bg-surface p-4 shadow-sm">
      <p className="text-sm font-medium text-primary">bg-surface</p>
    </div>
  </VStack>
</main>
```

### Global styles

Single file: `src/app/styles.css` â€” do not add page-specific global CSS unless necessary.

### Responsive design

- Tailwind responsive prefixes on layout wrappers (`max-w-3xl`, `grid grid-cols-3`, `min-h-screen`)
- Astryx layout components handle internal spacing via token `gap` props
- Figma dev-mode spacing â†’ nearest `MaNaReD.space.*` token â†’ `gap={n}` or `p-{n}`

